text: Zaw Min Latt (, born 12 April 1974), also known as Ko Latt, is a Burmese politician currently serving as a House of Nationalities MP representing the Shan State No. 1 constituency. He is a member of National League for Democracy. ==Early life and career== He was born on 12 April 1974 in Shwebo, Sagaing Region, Burma (Myanmar). He graduated with B.E (Mechanical), MIT from Mandalay Technological University. His previous job was as a trader. ==Political career== He is a member of the National League for Democracy. In the 2015 Myanmar general election, he was elected to the Amyotha Hluttaw, winning a majority of 226919 votes from the Shan State No. 1 parliamentary constituency. ==References== Category:Members of the House of Nationalities Category: National League for Democracy politicians Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:People from Sagaing Region Category:People from Shan State
